          <div class="row-fluid">
             <div class="span12">
               <h2>About the Project</h2>
               <p>I7UP was developed as a California Polytechnic State Universiy, San Luis Obispo senior project.  The software was designed around the idea of increasing the usability of Inform 7 text adventures: specifically, trying to remove the infamous verb-hunting that many users do.</p>
               <h3>Technologies</h3>
               <p>I7UP makes use of a number of technologies to accomplish its task.</p>
               <h4>Django</h4>
               <p>Django is the Web framework we use to populate website templates and send web pages; additioally, it acts as the bridge to process the unicode input with the specific Python-specific natural language tools we used.</p>
               <h4>NLTK</h4>
               NLTK is the Natural Language Toolkit - on of the leading platforms for Python to work with human language data.  Our program uses NLTK in order to find synonyms for words following a specific Inform 7 sentence format.
               <h4>Nodebox</h4>
